# Changelog

## 2.0.x

- **Breaking: Redis wire format has changed.** Existing cache entries written
  by 1.x are not readable by 2.0.x and must be dropped before upgrading.
  Use `(memento.redis/nuke!! #'your.memoized/function)` from an application
  process configured with the same Redis connection and key generator as the
  cache. Run once per distinct connection / `:memento.redis/keygen`. Only
  cached data is removed; values are recomputed on demand. See the README
  "Upgrade Warning" section for details.
- Requires Memento 2.1.74 or later.
- Cached `nil` values now round-trip correctly and remain visible in `as-map`.
- `if-cached` no longer blocks on in-flight loads and no longer rethrows
  loader exceptions; it returns the absent sentinel when no completed entry
  is available.
- Same-JVM callers arriving while a load is in flight now reliably coalesce
  onto the in-flight load instead of starting a redundant one.
- Improved cleanup of load markers and tag-invalidation metadata on
  invalidation and on stale-tag rejection.

## 1.1.30

- Update for Memento 2.1.x invalidation epoch APIs.
- Add Redis cache epoch key helpers for upcoming Redis-authoritative tag invalidation.
- Tag-aware invalidation is now Redis-authoritative: a per-cache epoch counter and
  per-tag-id epoch hash are kept in Redis, and loaders consult them in the
  finish-load Lua script. A load whose tags were invalidated mid-flight is
  rejected and joiners re-loop instead of caching a stale value.
- Pub/Sub invalidation channel bumped to `mem-redis-inval-v2` to accommodate the
  new payload shape. Rolling restarts across this version boundary will see
  invalidations propagate only within each cohort until the cutover completes;
  on-disk entry format is unchanged.

## 1.0.24

- moved to Java 11

## 0.5.23

- bump Carmine dep to latest
- added more tests
- added Redis Pub/Sub listener that will listen for sec index invalidations from foreign JVMs
- fix for secondary index maintenance

## 0.4.22

- complete rewrite of loader in Java
- fixes issues with concurrent access to same keys triggering multiple Redis accesses, important concurrency fixes
- if an exception is thrown by the cached function, all threads awaiting the same key will get the same exception at once, before each thread would attempt to call the function serially
- specify per entry TTL with `:memento.redis/ttl-fn`
- specify expiry on function bind instead of cache
- invalidations during the load will cause value to be recalculated

## 0.3.21

- add compatibility with Memento 1.2.x

## 0.2.20

- added support for detecting cache hits and misses
